{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 22:32:48.452320", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nScope and Topology\n- Fabric: 3-tier Clos (EBGP everywhere). Super-spine (AS65000) to spines, spines to leaves, each leaf to a single /24 host subnet.\n- Devices in scope: Hosts pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2/24 via 10.0.0.1), pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2/24 via 10.0.1.1); Leaves leaf_router_0_0, leaf_router_0_1; Spines spine_router_0_0, spine_router_0_1; Super-spine super_spine_router_0.\n\nSummary of Findings\n- Control plane is healthy: All EBGP sessions up across leaves, spines, and super-spine; full route coverage present throughout.\n- Data plane is healthy for pc_0_1 and the rest of the fabric.\n- Isolated outage: pc_0_0 cannot reach its default gateway (10.0.0.1) and cannot be reached from its leaf. Root cause is on pc_0_0: an active netem queue discipline with 60% packet corruption on eth0.\n\nEvidence and Observations\n\n1) Reachability and host-level tests\n- pc_0_0 → pc_0_1: TIMEOUT (both directions timed out when tested).\n- pc_0_0 → 10.0.0.1 (default gateway): TIMEOUT.\n- pc_0_1 → 10.0.1.1 (default gateway): OK (2/2, ~0.6 ms).\n\nHost configs:\n- pc_0_0: 10.0.0.2/24, default via 10.0.0.1, eth0 UP.\n- pc_0_1: 10.0.1.2/24, default via 10.0.1.1, eth0 UP.\n\n2) Leaf-to-host reachability\n- leaf_router_0_0 → 10.0.0.2: TIMEOUT (2/2 lost).\n- leaf_router_0_1 → 10.0.1.2: OK (2/2, ~0.48 ms).\n\nARP/Neighbor on leaves:\n- leaf_router_0_0 eth4 (10.0.0.1/24): ARP shows 10.0.0.2 lladdr a2:f0:96:e8:5b:23 STALE.\n- leaf_router_0_1 eth4 (10.0.1.1/24): ARP shows 10.0.1.2 lladdr e2:1f:5c:91:b0:4e DELAY (normal transient).\n\nInterpretation: The leaf for 10.0.0.0/24 knows pc_0_0’s MAC but is not receiving usable replies (STALE), consistent with a unidirectional reply failure from pc_0_0.\n\n3) Control plane (BGP) health across fabric\n- leaf_router_0_0 and leaf_router_0_1: 4 neighbors each (spines) UP; each has all pod and remote /24s via spines, and their local /24 connected.\n- spines: 6 neighbors each (2 super-spine + 4 leaves) UP; ECMP routes for remote subnets via super-spines and per-leaf routes for local subnets.\n- super_spine_router_0: 8 neighbors UP; has all /24s installed via appropriate spines.\n\nRouting tables on all routers show full and consistent coverage for all /24 host networks and interconnect /31s, indicating no control-plane or fabric-wide data-plane issues.\n\n4) Link/Interface condition on pc_0_0\n- tc qdisc on pc_0_0 eth0:\n  qdisc netem ... corrupt 60%\nThis indicates that 60% of pc_0_0’s outbound packets on eth0 are being corrupted intentionally by a netem impairment. Since netem acts on egress from pc_0_0:\n- Requests from pc_0_0 (e.g., ICMP Echo to 10.0.0.1) are frequently corrupted and dropped by the gateway due to checksum failures.\n- Replies to pings initiated by the leaf (leaf_router_0_0 → 10.0.0.2) require a response from pc_0_0; those responses are often corrupted on egress and thus never return successfully.\n\nAnomaly Detection\n- Yes. Severe connectivity impairment isolated to host pc_0_0. All other fabric components and pc_0_1 behave normally. No anomalies detected in EBGP adjacencies or routing.\n\nFault Localization\n- Fault localized to pc_0_0, specifically its eth0 transmit path.\n\nRoot Cause\n- Misconfiguration on pc_0_0: netem queue discipline configured with “corrupt 60%” on eth0, causing widespread packet corruption and effective communication failure for pc_0_0. This manifests as:\n  - pc_0_0 unable to reach its default gateway.\n  - The leaf’s ARP entry for pc_0_0 remains STALE and pings from the leaf to pc_0_0 fail due to corrupted replies.\n  - Cross-host communication involving pc_0_0 fails for the same reason.\n\nOverall Network Health Assessment\n- Fabric control plane (EBGP) and routing: Healthy.\n- Data plane across leaves/spines/super-spine: Healthy.\n- Host segments: 10.0.1.0/24 healthy; 10.0.0.0/24 leaf side is healthy, but host pc_0_0 is impaired due to local qdisc configuration.\n- Impact: Connectivity for pc_0_0 is severely degraded; other endpoints are unaffected.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 11777, "output_tokens": 3482, "total_tokens": 15259, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 11648}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2240}}}
